        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 3:43PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 342 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Ricardo, or 9 miles east of Premont, moving
southwest at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Kingsville, Premont, La Gloria, and Ricardo.

This includes the following highways...
US Highway 281 between mile markers 694 and 708.
US Highway 77 between mile markers 696 and 702.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
